scale(x, i) returns x * radix(x)**i.

default real examples:
x = -3.5
  scale(x,  1) = -7
  scale(x, -1) = -1.75
  scale(x,  2) = -14
x = -1
  scale(x,  1) = -2
  scale(x, -1) = -0.5
  scale(x,  2) = -4
x = -0.5
  scale(x,  1) = -1
  scale(x, -1) = -0.25
  scale(x,  2) = -2
x = 0
  scale(x,  1) = 0
  scale(x, -1) = 0
  scale(x,  2) = 0
x = 0.5
  scale(x,  1) = 1
  scale(x, -1) = 0.25
  scale(x,  2) = 2
x = 1
  scale(x,  1) = 2
  scale(x, -1) = 0.5
  scale(x,  2) = 4
x = 3.5
  scale(x,  1) = 7
  scale(x, -1) = 1.75
  scale(x,  2) = 14

kind examples:
scale(1.5,   3) = 12
scale(1.5_4, 3) = 12
scale(1.5_8, 3) = 12

using exponent:
x = -3.5  exponent(x) = 2  scale(fraction(x), exponent(x)) = -3.5
x = -1  exponent(x) = 1  scale(fraction(x), exponent(x)) = -1
x = -0.5  exponent(x) = 0  scale(fraction(x), exponent(x)) = -0.5
x = 0.5  exponent(x) = 0  scale(fraction(x), exponent(x)) = 0.5
x = 1  exponent(x) = 1  scale(fraction(x), exponent(x)) = 1
x = 3.5  exponent(x) = 2  scale(fraction(x), exponent(x)) = 3.5
